Step 1: Draw a diagonal of the rectangle. By the Pythagorean theorem, the length of the diagonal is sqrt(6^2+8^2)=10 centimeters. Also, by symmetry the diagonal of the rectangle is a diameter of the circle. The circumference of the circle is pi* (diameter)=10pi centimeters. [asy]
