Step 9: label("D",(-60,0),S);
Step 10: label("C",(166,0),S);
Step 11: label("50^",(3.5,0),NE);
Step 12: [/asy] Since the sum of the angles in triangle ABC is 180^ and we know two angles 93^ and 50^ which add to 143^, then ACB = 180^ - 143^ = 37^.
Answer: 37^

